<apex:page sidebar="false" showHeader="false" applyHtmlTag="false" applyBodyTag="false" standardStylesheets="false" renderAs="pdf" controller="HIPApplicationCtrl">
    <html>
    <head>
        <style type="text/css">
            @page {
                margin: 0.65in;
                size: letter;
            }
            body {
                font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
                font-size: 13.5pt;
                color: #222;
                line-height: 1.34;
            }
            .header {
                min-height: 80px;
                margin-bottom: 12px;
            }
            .logo {
                width: 96px;
                height: auto;
            }
            p {
                margin: 0 0 14px;
            }
            .salutation {
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            .section-title {
                margin: 8px 0 10px;
                font-size: 17pt;
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            .income-title {
                margin: 12px 0 16px;
                text-align: center;
                text-decoration: underline;
                font-size: 16pt;
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            .income-grid {
                width: 100%;
                margin: 0 0 16px;
            }
            .income-grid td {
                width: 33%;
                vertical-align: top;
                font-weight: bold;
                padding-bottom: 6px;
            }
            ul {
                margin: 0 0 14px 22px;
            }
            ul li {
                margin: 0 0 6px;
            }
            .center-address {
                margin-top: 90px;
                text-align: center;
                font-size: 18pt;
                font-weight: bold;
                line-height: 1.25;
            }
            .center-note {
                margin-top: 170px;
                text-align: center;
            }
            .check-list {
                list-style: none;
                margin: 0 0 14px;
                padding: 0;
            }
            .check-list li {
                margin: 0 0 7px;
                padding-left: 22px;
                position: relative;
            }
            .check-list li:before {
                content: "";
                position: absolute;
                left: 0;
                top: 6px;
                width: 10px;
                height: 10px;
                border: 1.5px solid #666;
            }
            .red-note {
                text-align: center;
                color: #c5261b;
                font-weight: bold;
                margin: 10px 0 16px;
            }
            .final-note {
                margin-top: 90px;
                text-align: center;
                font-weight: bold;
            }
            .page-break {
                page-break-before: always;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="header">
            <apex:image value="{!logoUrl}" rendered="{!logoUrl != null}" styleClass="logo"/>
        </div>

        <p class="salutation">Dear Homeowner,</p>

        <p>
            Thank you for your interest in Galvan Housing Resources' Home Improvement Program.
            GHR provides matching grants for project costs to assist low to moderate-income
            homeowners in completing necessary health and safety-related repairs and improvements
            to their homes. Pre-qualified contractors will complete improvements after an open and
            competitive bidding process.
        </p>

        <p>
            The primary threshold requirements for participation are that the recipient household
            must own the subject property and maintain it as their principal place of residence at
            the time of application. Further, the participant household must earn no more than 80%
            of the Columbia County median income adjusted by family size according to the most
            recently published U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) median
            income data:
        </p>

        <div class="income-title">*2025 Income Limits (by family size)</div>

        <table class="income-grid" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
            <tr>
                <td>1 Person: $63,150</td>
                <td>4 Person: $90,150</td>
                <td>7 Person: $111,800</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>2 Person: $72,150</td>
                <td>5 Person: $97,400</td>
                <td>8 Person: $119,000</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>3 Person: $81,150</td>
                <td>6 Person: $104,600</td>
                <td></td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <p>
            Examples of work that can be done on a home to bring a structure into compliance with
            applicable laws and regulations, include but are not limited to the following:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>Installation, replacement or repair of heating, plumbing, electrical, and related systems</li>
            <li>Work to improve habitability or prolong the useful life of the home</li>
            <li>Roof repairs</li>
            <li>Elimination of all hazardous materials and violations</li>
            <li>General structural repairs</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            The Home Improvement Program Grant is a matching grant. Galvan Housing Resources has
            executed an agreement with Columbia Opportunities Inc. to provide matching services under
            their Weatherization program.
        </p>

        <p>
            Please complete, sign, and date the enclosed application and return it to address below.
            Once received, we will contact you to set up a time to review the information.
        </p>

        <div class="page-break"></div>
        <div class="header">
            <apex:image value="{!logoUrl}" rendered="{!logoUrl != null}" styleClass="logo"/>
        </div>
        <div class="center-address">
            <div>Galvan Housing Resources,</div>
            <div>64 Green Street,</div>
            <div>Hudson, NY 12534</div>
            <div>Attn: Susan Petersen</div>
        </div>
        <p class="center-note">*income limits good until May 2026</p>

        <div class="page-break"></div>
        <div class="header">
            <apex:image value="{!logoUrl}" rendered="{!logoUrl != null}" styleClass="logo"/>
        </div>
        <div class="section-title">Recapture/Compliance Requirements:</div>
        <p>
            Certain occupancy restrictions, secured by a subordinate mortgage, apply to recipients
            of Home Improvement Program (HIP) grants. These grant funds will be secured by a note and
            mortgage for 2-15 years, depending on the amount of funds, with no required repayment as
            long as you remain in and are the owner of the house for the required length of time.
        </p>

        <div class="section-title">The following information MUST be attached to the application:</div>
        <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Proof of Home ownership (legible copy of recorded deed)</li>
            <li>Proof of Homeowner's insurance (recent declaration page/recent certificate from agent)</li>
            <li>Copies of most recent paid Property, Town and Village AND School tax receipt</li>
            <li>Most recent mortgage statement, if applicable. The mortgage must be paid up to date.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="red-note">Please use boxes to check off items once attached</p>

        <div class="section-title">Plus: For EACH household member 18 years and older:</div>
        <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Proof of income from all sources - 2 months of current and consecutive pay stubs, statements from SS, SSD, SSI, child support, alimony, DSS assistance, etc.</li>
            <li>Completed, signed and dated copies of the most recent FEDERAL tax returns and W2's (2024 and 2025) OR a notarized statement of non-filing of tax returns, if applicable</li>
            <li>Three most recent bank statements for each bank account per household member</li>
            <li>Recent whole life insurance policy (if applicable) statement showing the cash surrender value (term life policies are excluded)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="page-break"></div>
        <div class="header">
            <apex:image value="{!logoUrl}" rendered="{!logoUrl != null}" styleClass="logo"/>
        </div>
        <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Recent statements showing your name and your balance of ALL peer-to-peer payment apps including but not limited to: VenMo, Zelle, CashApp, Paypal, etc.</li>
            <li>Copies of most recent utility bills and monthly debt obligations, i.e., electric, phone, etc.</li>
            <li>Completed Financial Assessment (page 9)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="final-note">Incomplete applications will not be accepted</p>
    </body>
    </html>
</apex:page>
